<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1440,771,1051]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<keyLead pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
1. Postclypeus flat, fastigium at nearly right angle (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[1064,1132,771,795]" captionStart="Figure 1-6" captionStartId="3.[196,280,1000,1022]" captionTargetBox="[192,1424,197,954]" captionTargetId="figure-367@3.[192,1442,194,980]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1-6. Issidae. 1) Aztecus mexicanus (Kirkaldy), syntype, head in ventral view. 2) Argepara semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, female, lateral view. 3) A. semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, male, head in ventral view. 4) Argepara lyra (Berg), female, lateral view (Argentina). 5) Same, head in ventral view. 6) Same, melanistic form, dorsal view (Paraguay)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532903/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); head and dorsum brown or dark brown excluding pale costal margins of fore wings (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1137,803,827]" captionStart="Figure 1-6" captionStartId="3.[196,280,1000,1022]" captionTargetBox="[192,1424,197,954]" captionTargetId="figure-367@3.[192,1442,194,980]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1-6. Issidae. 1) Aztecus mexicanus (Kirkaldy), syntype, head in ventral view. 2) Argepara semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, female, lateral view. 3) A. semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, male, head in ventral view. 4) Argepara lyra (Berg), female, lateral view (Argentina). 5) Same, head in ventral view. 6) Same, melanistic form, dorsal view (Paraguay)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532903/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 2, 3</figureCitation>
); hind margin of pygofer without apical process (
<figureCitation box="[591,674,835,859]" captionStart="Figure 33-37" captionStartId="11.[192,276,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[200,1437,196,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[192,1439,191,1774]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 33-37. Argepara semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, male genitalia. 33) Pygofer, anal tube, and aedeagus, lateral view. 34) Aedeagus, ventral view. 35) Style, lateral view. 36) Capitulum of style, dorsal view. 37) Anal tube, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532915" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532915/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
); capitulum of style without subapical tooth (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 33-37" captionStartId="11.[192,276,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[200,1437,196,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[192,1439,191,1774]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 33-37. Argepara semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, male genitalia. 33) Pygofer, anal tube, and aedeagus, lateral view. 34) Aedeagus, ventral view. 35) Style, lateral view. 36) Capitulum of style, dorsal view. 37) Anal tube, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532915" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532915/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) ............................................................................................. 
