<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1440,771,1051]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<keyLead pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
— Postclypeus strongly convex, forming a cone-shaped projection, fastigium at obtuse angle (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[477,547,931,955]" captionStart="Figure 1-6" captionStartId="3.[196,280,1000,1022]" captionTargetBox="[192,1424,197,954]" captionTargetId="figure-367@3.[192,1442,194,980]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1-6. Issidae. 1) Aztecus mexicanus (Kirkaldy), syntype, head in ventral view. 2) Argepara semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, female, lateral view. 3) A. semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, male, head in ventral view. 4) Argepara lyra (Berg), female, lateral view (Argentina). 5) Same, head in ventral view. 6) Same, melanistic form, dorsal view (Paraguay)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532903/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); head and dorsum from dark brown to black with median yellow vitta thru metope to wing tip (reduced in melanistic specimens) (
<figureCitation box="[958,1054,963,987]" captionStart="Figure 1-6" captionStartId="3.[196,280,1000,1022]" captionTargetBox="[192,1424,197,954]" captionTargetId="figure-367@3.[192,1442,194,980]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1-6. Issidae. 1) Aztecus mexicanus (Kirkaldy), syntype, head in ventral view. 2) Argepara semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, female, lateral view. 3) A. semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, male, head in ventral view. 4) Argepara lyra (Berg), female, lateral view (Argentina). 5) Same, head in ventral view. 6) Same, melanistic form, dorsal view (Paraguay)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532903/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5, 6</figureCitation>
), with costal and median stripes joining at wing apex (
<figureCitation box="[561,628,995,1019]" captionStart="Figure 1-6" captionStartId="3.[196,280,1000,1022]" captionTargetBox="[192,1424,197,954]" captionTargetId="figure-367@3.[192,1442,194,980]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1-6. Issidae. 1) Aztecus mexicanus (Kirkaldy), syntype, head in ventral view. 2) Argepara semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, female, lateral view. 3) A. semipellucida (Melichar), syntype, male, head in ventral view. 4) Argepara lyra (Berg), female, lateral view (Argentina). 5) Same, head in ventral view. 6) Same, melanistic form, dorsal view (Paraguay)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532903/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); hind margin of pygofer with large apical process (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1300,995,1019]" captionStart="Figure 38-42" captionStartId="13.[192,276,1795,1817]" captionTargetBox="[201,1435,197,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[190,1444,191,1756]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 38-42. Argepara lyra (Berg), male genitalia. 38) Pygofer, anal tube, and aedeagus, lateral view. 39) Aedeagus, ventral view. 40) Style, lateral view. 41) Capitulum of style, dorsal view. 42) Anal tube, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532917/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
); capitulum of style with large subapical tooth (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[928,1012,1027,1051]" captionStart="Figure 38-42" captionStartId="13.[192,276,1795,1817]" captionTargetBox="[201,1435,197,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[190,1444,191,1756]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 38-42. Argepara lyra (Berg), male genitalia. 38) Pygofer, anal tube, and aedeagus, lateral view. 39) Aedeagus, ventral view. 40) Style, lateral view. 41) Capitulum of style, dorsal view. 42) Anal tube, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532917/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
) ............................. 
